<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-07-17T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-07-17T05:00:00-05:00" n="129" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Great Britain/6:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-17T11:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">July 17,
                                        1922—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July 17—7:20
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>295. The Embassy is officially informed by the Foreign Office that a
                            special delegation will proceed to the United States early in September
                            to negotiate terms for the funding of the British debt to the United
                            States.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harvey</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>